{
  "texts": [
    "We utilized a novel convolutional neural network called PlexusNet 44 that supports neural architecture search (NAS) 45 and uses ResNet 46 and Inception blocks 47 as well as standard convolutional blocks (VGGs).",
    "Taking inspiration from a previous study, we also included quasisoft attention blocks 48 (we removed \"quasi\" from the block description for convenience).",
    "The PlexusNet architecture is a directed acyclic multigraph.",
    "The complexity of this graph is primarily determined by its depth (i.e., the number of levels), extent of branching (i.e., end-toend paths or width) and number of weighted junctions (i.e., cross edges) between two end-to-end paths that give rise to the multigraph property.",
    "A transitory \"short\" path was randomly defined to populate feature maps of an end-to-end path at a random level (Fig. 6)."
  ]
}